						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone (No. II) set up near the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>Tailapa II [A.D. 981].</p>						

						<p>This inscription belonging to the reign of Tailapa is dated Śaka 903, Vishuva, Vaiśākha, 10. Thursday, Uttarā. The date is identical to that of the previous record.</p>						

						<p>It records the death of <hi rend="italic">gōsāsi</hi> Dugaṇa in a cattle-raid, when Eṟegāri was holding the office of <hi rend="italic">Nāl-gāvuṇḍu</hi> and Eṟechaṭṭa was holding the office of <hi rend="italic">Ūr-gāvuṇḍu.</hi> Aṇnayya wrote the record.</p>						

						</summary>
